                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>subscribed for, for instance <persName>Elias</persName> said he subscribed for<lb/> a\n                Bible you have him prayer Books <persName>Mr Levin</persName> ditto.<lb/> Then again\n                there is dissatisfaction as regards the price<lb/> charged <persName>Mr.\n                    Wolf</persName> wrote me he put his name down<lb/> for five or six dollar Bible\n                &amp; others say the prices<lb/> are higher than the subscription list called for.<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. Elias</persName> tells me <persName>Mr. Summer</persName> brought\n                several<lb/> setts of the Prayer Books home with him for which<lb/> he paid 15.00\n                for such as you charge 18.00 he did<lb/> not say positively they were bought of you\n                but<lb/> were your books he says he would have no<lb/> objection purchasing a\n                    <sic>sett</sic> but will not pay<lb/> your price. <persName>Mrs Levin</persName>\n                says she will either take<lb/> a Bible or a <sic>sett</sic> of P Books I know not\n                which<lb/> she was to have let me known which she would<lb/> take for the last ten\n                days There are three odd<lb/> Vols of prayer books presume packed in mistake<lb/>\n                could have sold the <date>kippur</date> but the price I asked<lb/> was said to be\n                too high the average being 4.50.<lb/> I have on hand 2 <sic>sett</sic> P B. 27 ch. 1\n                    <sic>sett</sic> $25 00<lb/> 1 Bible 12. 2 Bibles 8 ch 5\n                    <persName>Dias</persName>. The balance I<lb/> have included in the <add>?</add>\n                check</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr L</persName> &amp; the children are all well &amp; send\n                kind<lb/> remembrance to you. All the children you have named<lb/> correctly but you\n                have left out of the list the <add>?</add><lb/> child doubt much if his equal was\n                ever born—his<lb/> name is <persName>Charles Henry</persName> &amp; you may think\n                yourself fortunate<lb/> if his mother ever forgives the slight you have put on</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cf9js9k/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
